About
=====

  This directory contains simple example programs that show how to use
  libprimesieve to generate, count and print primes and prime
  k-tuplets.

  The example programs are documented in ../doc/EXAMPLES,
  ../doc/LIBPRIMESIEVE explains how to build libprimesieve in more
  detail.

How to compile the example programs
===================================

  Open a terminal or 'Visual Studio Command Prompt' and cd into the
  primesieve directory. The following commands build and install
  libprimesieve and then compile the example programs.

  Microsoft Visual C++
  --------------------

  > nmake -f Makefile.msvc lib
  > nmake -f Makefile.msvc examples

  Unix-like OSes, `c++' compiler
  ------------------------------

  $ make lib
  $ sudo make install
  $ make examples

  Unix-like OSes, other C++ compilers
  -----------------------------------

  e.g. Intel C++ compiler:

  $ make lib CXX=icpc CXXFLAGS="-O2 -openmp"
  $ sudo make install
  $ make examples CXX=icpc CXXFLAGS="-O2 -openmp"
